The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 599) The British band Travis returns to its 

 hometown in Glasgow for a great performance. Almost all 

 the songs from the first album (Good Feeling) are 

 performed as well as tracks from Invisible Band. 

 Catch the crowd sing along as loud as it can. 

 THE TV SHOW

 (Cartoon Network, July 10, 11.30 am) If you were a fan 

 of Batman: The Animated Series, you can?t afford 

 to miss this one. The caped crusader?s eternal fight against 

 Joker, Penguin, Mr Freeze and Riddler continues, as the 

 vigilante strives for a safer Gotham. 

 THE TALK

 (Bengal 

 Club, 7.30 pm, July 16) The chat will have actress Supriya 

 Debi taking a trip down memory lane into the golden years 

 of Bengali cinema. Giving her company will be actors Suchita 

 Raychaudhury and Arindam Sil among others. Conceived by Sujoy 

 Prosad Chatterjee, the show will also include some music by 

 Arati Mukherjee, Saikat Mitra and others. 




